**LTI (Learning Tools Interoperability)** is a **1EdTech** standard that lets a learning platform (LMS) integrate remote tools and content in a standard way.

**LTI 1.3** (Core spec version 3, issued **16 April 2019**) modernized security: it **replaced OAuth 1.0a message signing** with **OpenID Connect**, **signed JWTs**, and **OAuth 2.0** workflows.

On top of Core 1.3 sit the **LTI Advantage** services:
- **Deep Linking 2.0** — pick content from the tool inside the LMS;
- **Names & Role Provisioning Services (NRPS) 2.0** — securely share the **course roster**;
- **Assignment & Grade Services (AGS) 2.0** — write grades back to the LMS gradebook.
